                            .:DESCRiPTiON:.                             
                                                                          
                                                                          
    Test your reflexes by punching Twittering Birds!                      
                                                                          
    Imagine you are enjoying a nice sunny day in the beautiful            
    countryside. You lie down under the tree ready to take a quick nap.   
    .. Suddenly there are disturbing noises from above! What?!? Those     
    little birdies are twittering like mad. If you could only punch       
    them so they stay quiet... Now you can! New iPhone game Bird Reflex   
    lets you test your reflexes by punching those crazy twittering        
    birds... See how fast your reactions are in two game modes: In        
    Reflex Mode there will be 10 birds randomly falling from the tree.    
    Your goal is to punch the bird as soon as she leaves the tree but     
    not too early and not too late, because there will be penalties. In   
    Time Mode you have to keep little worm alive as long as you can.      
    Every birdie you don't punch will bite the worm a little. If you're   
    really really fast you'll gain various game achievements. Happy       
    punching! FEATURES:  Very fast and reflex demanding gameplay         
     Two game challenges: reflex mode & time mode                        
     Real-time Chat with friends & worldwide community                   
     Worldwide scores powered by Open Feint                              
     Facebook & Twitter shared achievements                              
     Global, local and friends leaderboards                              
     Find new friends directly from the game                             
     Amazing original graphics, music and sound                          
                                                                          
                                                                          
                                                                          
    What's new                                                            
     Added possibility to view scores and achievements of your Twitter   
    and Face Book friends  Added possibility to compare your scores      
    and achievements with friends  Improved support for offline high     
    scores
